
## Day- 6

ðŸŽ¯ Interview Problem
Find users who placed orders on at least 3 consecutive days.

Strict rules:

Consecutive = calendar days
Use order_date (not order_id)
Output only user_id
Each user appears once

ðŸ‘‰ Write the SQL query.

ðŸ§© SQL Solution
WITH t AS (
    SELECT
        user_id,
        order_date,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY user_id
            ORDER BY order_date
        ) AS rn
    FROM orders
),
grp AS (
    SELECT
        user_id,
        order_date,
        order_date - rn AS grp_id
    FROM t
)
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM grp
GROUP BY user_id, grp_id
HAVING COUNT(*) >= 3;

ðŸ“Œ Interview Insight

This problem tests:
Pattern recognition
Date arithmetic
Grouping consecutive records

If you know why order_date - row_number() works,
youâ€™re already ahead of most candidates.

